<title>COLOMBIA: Cemento Argos first-half net drops 47 pct.</title>
<headline>Cemento Argos first-half net drops 47 pct.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA 1997-07-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Colombia's largest cement company Cemento Argos on Friday said first-half net profit fell 47 percent to 26.6 billion pesos compared with the same period last year.</p>
<p>In the first half of 1996, the company had sold stocks worth about 19 billion pesos.  </p>
<p>Argos said operating profits rose 412 percent to 1.97 billion pesos in the first half, and operating climbed a 14 percent to 13 billion pesos.</p>
<p>((--Karl Penhaul, Bogota newsroom, 571 610 7944))</p>
